The paper deals with visual data augmentation, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves learning transformations that map images to a latent space, which is a common approach in deep learning and generative models (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of these transformations to create new images that can be considered two successive frames in a video, which relates to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
